{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QC1em9CwYGbK7zGsGg5D2Q","type":"tool_result","content":"   880→\n   881→Ralph: BROKEN. 44 consecutive no-op sessions. ~$103 burned on the same fix. Combined with unattributed overhead ($175.76) and phantom cost ($24.35), total identifiable waste is ~$303 — 41% of the $738.35 sprint budget.\n   882→\n   883→The retro mechanism cannot stop Ralph. This is the 44th retro saying the same thing. Kill the process manually or add an exit condition. There is no other path.\n   884→\n   885→---\n   886→\n   887→## Session 61 — Sprint Complete, No-Op #45\n   888→\n   889→**Date:** 2026-03-28T06:00Z\n   890→**Session:** 61\n   891→**Sprint status:** COMPLETE -- 74/74 stories done, 17/17 epics done\n   892→**Productive work this session:** None. State corruption fix only.\n   893→\n   894→---\n   895→\n   896→### 1. Session Summary\n   897→\n   898→No-op session. The sprint has been 100% complete since session 30. This session's only activity was fixing state corruption for the 45th consecutive time. Ralph's stale in-memory state reverted stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from `done` to `review` and epic-16 from `done` to `backlog`, dropping the done count from 74 to 70. The fix was applied. No other work was performed because no work remains.\n   899→\n   900→### 2. Issues Analysis -- The Recurring State Corruption\n   901→\n   902→**Root cause (unchanged since session 17):** Ralph loads `sprint-state.json` into memory at startup. Its in-memory snapshot predates the completion of stories 16-5 through 16-8. On each loop iteration, Ralph writes its stale in-memory state back to disk, overwriting the corrected state. The `registerStory` guard added in session 22 prevents phantom story injection but does not prevent status reversion of existing stories.\n   903→\n   904→**Pattern every session:**\n   905→1. Ralph loop starts, loads stale state (70/74 done)\n   906→2. Ralph writes stale state to `sprint-state.json`\n   907→3. Session detects regression: 4 stories reverted, epic-16 reverted\n   908→4. Session fixes state back to 74/74\n   909→5. Session writes retro saying \"stop Ralph\"\n   910→6. Ralph loops again. Goto 1.\n   911→\n   912→This is the 45th occurrence. The cycle is self-sustaining because the retro mechanism has no authority to stop Ralph.\n   913→\n   914→**Evidence from `ralph/status.json` (still stale):**\n   915→- `stories_completed: 70` (should be 74)\n   916→- `stories_remaining: 4` (should be 0)\n   917→\n   918→### 3. Cost Analysis\n   919→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01B7k7CZgfSVRuqdhLNcKLJQ","session_id":"b1570512-e586-4f79-8879-7bf12fc4c72d","uuid":"400ea58b-81b3-4026-8828-3121eaed6937","timestamp":"2026-03-28T06:35:45.669Z"}
